      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, i'm working on a research paper and i keep getting told my writing is too passive. can u help me figure out how to spot it and fix it? like maybe with an example?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'd be happy to help you identify and address passive voice in your writing. Passive voice is written where the subject receives the action, rather than performing it. To spot passive voice, look for verbs in forms like \"was\" or \"were,\" or vague phrases like \"it was decided that\" or \"the author states.\" Example: \"The report was written by John\" can be rewritten as \"John wrote the report.\"",
